    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Neckwear comprising narrow strips of fabric, typically white in color and sometimes trimmed with lace, that are basted as liners inside the neck of an ecclesiastical stole or other similar non-ecclesiastical garment to protect it from soiling due to contact with the skin. For medium-sized to large outerwear collars that resemble fashion stoles, use "stole collars (outerwear collars)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
